Input:  Turkey  percentageOfAreaWater  1.3   Output:   Q: How can I make this code faster? I have a piece of code that is slowing down my program significantly. It calculates the similarity between two strings using Levenshtein distance. The problem is that I need to calculate the similarity for every string in a list against every other string in the list. Here is the code:  from scipy.spatial.distance import levenshtein  def calc_similarity(strings: List[str]) -> List[List[float]]:      result = []      for i in range(len(strings)):          row = []          for j in range(len(strings)):              if i == j:                  row.append(1)              else:                  row.append(levenshtein(strings[i], strings[j]))          result.append(row)      return result  This function takes a list of strings as input and returns a list of lists, where each inner list represents the similarity between the string at the same index in the input list and all other strings in the list.  For example, if the input list is ['cat', 'cats', 'dog'], the output will be:  [[0, 1, 3],   [1, 0, 2],   [3, 2, 0]]  The

Here is what I have tried so far:  import discord  from discord.ext import commands  intents = discord.Intents.default()  intents.message_content = True  bot = commands.Bot(command_prefix="!", intents=intents)  @bot.event  async def on_message(message):      if message.content.lower() == "hello":          await message.channel.send("Hello back at you!")  bot.run('token')  However, this doesn't seem to be working. For years my hair has been thinning(not enough to shave it but enough to be noticeable). After about 3 months of using Nioxin, the thinning process seemed to stop. My hair is healthy and grows fairly fast. Some people might say that Nioxin "caused" my hair to stop thinning but I don't believe it. I think what happened was I hadn't found a shampoo that didn't further damage my hair until I started using Nioxin. So to those considering trying Nioxin, understand that it won't help if you continue to damage your hair(hot curlers, tight rubber bands, peroxide/dye, etc.). Also, understand that a little bit goes a long way. Even with daily use, one bottle lasts me over 6 months. By John Manganaro  The New York City Council has passed Intro 436-A, a bill that will require private-sector employers with at least 10 employees to automatically enroll workers in individual retirement accounts (IRAs) unless they already offer a retirement plan.  According to a press release from the office of New York City Council Speaker Melissa Mark-Viverito, the new law is designed to address the fact that "nearly half of all working New Yorkers have no access to a retirement savings plan through their employer."  "This legislation will level the playing field by ensuring that every hardworking New Yorker has the opportunity to save for their retirement," Mark-Viverito says. "For too long, our city's middle class and working families have been left out of the retirement security system, which is why we must take action now to make sure everyone has the tools they need to retire with dignity."  Under the terms of Intro 436-A, employers will be required

Tom Millward  Today marks 32 years since Andrew Lloyd Webber's The Phantom of the Opera first opened on Broadway at the Majestic Theatre. The production made its Broadway debut on January 26, 1988, following previews from January 9, 1988.  Based on the French novel Le Fantôme de l'Opéra by Gaston Leroux, The Phantom of the Opera features music by Andrew Lloyd Webber, lyrics by Charles Hart, and a book by Richard Stilgoe and Lloyd Webber. It tells the story of a disfigured musical genius known only as "The Phantom" who haunts the depths of the Paris Opera House. Mesmerized by the talent of the young soprano Christine, the Phantom lures her as his protégé and falls fiercely in love with her.  The original Broadway cast featured Michael Crawford as The Phantom, Sarah Brightman as Christine Daaé, Steve Barton as Raoul, and Rosemary Ashe as Carl

Input:  1147_Stavropolis  apoapsis  418476000000.0 ,  1147_Stavropolis  discoverer  Grigory_Neujmin   Output:   Q: How can I get the first day of current week in SQL Server? I want to get the first day of the current week in SQL Server.  How can I do this?  A: The simplest way is to use DATEADD() with DATEPART():  SELECT DATEADD(DAY, DATEDIFF(DAY, 0, GETDATE()) % 7, 0)  This returns the first day of the current week. It calculates the difference between the current date and the first day of the week (Sunday = 0, Monday = 1, etc.) using DATEDIFF(), then takes the remainder of that result when divided by 7. Finally, it subtracts that remainder from the first day of the week.  If you want the first day of the week to be Monday instead of Sunday, replace 0 with 1 in the above expression.  A: In SQL Server 2012+ you can use EOMONTH() and DATEFROMPARTS():  SELECT DATEFROMPARTS(YEAR(GETDATE()), EOMONTH(GETDATE(), 0) - DATEPART(WEEKDAY, GETDATE()) + 1, 1)  A: SELECT DATEADD(day, DATEDIFF(day, 0, GETDATE()) % 7,

Input:  Liselotte_Grschebina  nationality  Israel ,  Liselotte_Grschebina  training  School_of_Applied_Arts_in_Stuttgart ,  Liselotte_Grschebina  deathDate  1994-06-14   Output:   Q: How do I get the number of rows affected by a query? I am trying to get the number of rows affected by a query using mysql workbench. I have tried using SELECT LAST_INSERT_ID(); but it returns NULL.  Here is my query:  SET @id = (SELECT id FROM users WHERE email = 'myemail@gmail.com');  UPDATE users SET password = PASSWORD('mypassword') WHERE id = @id;  SELECT LAST_INSERT_ID();  A: The LAST_INSERT_ID() function returns the ID of the last row inserted into an AUTO_INCREMENT column in the current session and database.  In your case, there is no AUTO_INCREMENT column updated/inserted.  If you want to know how many rows were affected by the UPDATE statement, you can use the ROW_COUNT() function:  SET @id = (SELECT id FROM users WHERE email = 'myemail@gmail.com');  UPDATE users SET password = PASSWORD('mypassword') WHERE id = @id;  SELECT ROW_COUNT();  ROW_COUNT() returns the number of rows affected by the last DELETE, REPLACE, or UPDATE statement executed.

One CAI program used traditional drill and practice exercises, while the other used problem-solving activities. A total of 106 sixth grade students from two junior high schools participated in the study. Participants were randomly assigned to one of four groups: Traditional Drill and Practice CAI, Problem-Solving CAI, Traditional Drill and Practice Non-CAI, and Problem-Solving Non-CAI. Each group received 20 forty-five minute sessions of instruction over a ten week period. Students completed pretest and posttest measures of attitudes toward mathematics and achievement in mathematics. Results indicated that there were no significant differences between the four groups on either the pretest or posttest measures of attitudes toward mathematics. In addition, there were no significant differences between the four groups on the pretest measure of achievement in mathematics. On the posttest measure of achievement in mathematics, results indicated that students in the Traditional Drill and Practice CAI group had significantly higher scores than students in the Traditional Drill and Practice Non-CAI group. The research team found that overexpression of the gene, called LRIG3, was associated with more aggressive forms of prostate cancer, increased metastasis and decreased patient survival.  "LRIG3 is highly expressed in castration-resistant prostate cancer, which accounts for approximately 90 percent of advanced prostate cancers," said senior author Chandra Sekhar Pemmaraju, Ph.D., professor of Genomic Medicine and member of the Institute for Applied Cancer Science at MD Anderson. "Our findings suggest that LRIG3 could serve as a potential therapeutic target for this deadly disease."  Pemmaraju and his colleagues analyzed data from The Cancer Genome Atlas (TCGA)—a comprehensive catalog of genomic abnormalities across 33 different cancer types—and found that LRIG3 expression was significantly higher in prostate tumors compared to normal prostate tissues. They also found that high levels of LRIG3 were associated with poorer overall survival rates in patients with prostate cancer.  To further investigate

By John Manganaro  The Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC) has announced that an investment adviser firm has agreed to pay a $75,000 penalty to settle charges that it failed to adequately supervise its employees' compliance with certain marketing rules.  According to the SEC's order instituting a cease-and-desist proceeding, Tortoise Capital Advisors LLC violated the Investment Advisers Act of 1940 by failing to establish, maintain and enforce written policies and procedures reasonably designed to prevent violations of Rule 206(4)-3 under the Advisers Act, commonly known as the "Cash Solicitation Rule."  The Cash Solicitation Rule prohibits investment advisers from giving or agreeing to give cash or cash equivalent payments to a client or a client's broker-dealer for recommending or securing advisory business, subject to certain exceptions. It refers to investments made into companies that meet certain environmental, social, and corporate governance criteria. However, for companies themselves, managing their ESG risks is just as important.  The World Economic Forum estimates that ignoring ESG risks could lead to financial losses of up to $4.2 trillion by 2030. With such high stakes at play, companies need to have a comprehensive understanding of their ESG risks. This is where artificial intelligence (AI) comes into play.  Artificial intelligence can help companies identify, monitor, and manage their ESG risks more effectively. Here's how:  1. Data Collection and Analysis  Collecting and analyzing data related to ESG risks can be a time-consuming and resource-intensive task. AI can help automate this process, making it faster and more efficient. By using natural language processing and machine learning algorithms, AI systems can scan large volumes of data from various sources, including regulatory filings, news articles, and social media, to identify relevant ESG issues.  2. Risk Scoring and Prioritization

Input:  Michael_Rooker  birthDate  1955-04-06   Output:   Q: How to add multiple values into single cell in csv file using php? I want to add multiple values into single cell in csv file using php.  For example:  If i have array like this:  $array = array(1,2,3,4,5);  and i want to store this array into single cell in csv file.  Is there any way to do this using php?  A: Here is one way to do it:  <?php  $array = [1,2,3,4,5];  $csv = fopen('output.csv', 'w');  fputcsv($csv, $array);  fclose($csv);  ?>  This will create a CSV file called output.csv with one row and one column containing your array.  Note: The above code assumes that you are using PHP's built-in CSV handling functions (fopen(), fputcsv(), fclose()).

Is there a way to get the name of the last executed function in Python?  For example, let's say I have this code:  def foo():      print(get_last_executed_function_name())  def bar():      foo()  bar()  The output should be bar.  A: Use inspect.currentframe().f_back.f_code.co_name  from inspect import currentframe  def foo():      print(currentframe().f_back.f_code.co_name)  def bar():      foo()  bar()  # bar  A: You can use sys._getframe(1).f_back.f_code.co_name for getting the name of the previous function. Academic journal article Journal of Marriage and Family  The Effects of Parental Divorce on Children's Educational Attainment: Longitudinal Evidence From the National Longitudinal Study of Adolescent Health  By Amato, Paul R.; Sobolewski, Joseph T.  This study investigated the long-term effects of parental divorce on children's educational attainment using data from the National Longitudinal Study of Adolescent Health (Add Health). The analyses included 15,740 respondents who were followed from adolescence into young adulthood. We controlled for numerous family background variables, including family socioeconomic status, parental education, and parental monitoring. Results indicated that children of divorce were less likely to have graduated from high school by age 24 and were less likely to have earned a bachelor's degree by age 26. They also were less likely to have enrolled in college by age 24. These effects remained significant even when controlling for family background characteristics.  Divorce is associated with many negative outcomes for children (Amato, 1993, 1994, 1

Input:  Liselotte_Grschebina  birthPlace  German_Empire ,  Liselotte_Grschebina  training  School_of_Applied_Arts_in_Stuttgart ,  Liselotte_Grschebina  professionalField  Photographer   Output:   Q: How to calculate the number of ways to arrange $n$ distinct objects such that no two identical objects are adjacent to each other? There are $n$ distinct objects. I want to calculate the number of ways to arrange these objects such that no two identical objects are adjacent to each other.  For example, for $n=3$, there are $6$ arrangements:  123, 132, 213, 231, 312, 321  My attempt:  Let $a_n$ be the number of arrangements for $n$ distinct objects.  We can consider the first object. There are $n$ choices for the first object.  After choosing the first object, we have $a_{n-1}$ ways to arrange the remaining $n-1$ objects such that no two identical objects are adjacent to each other.  Therefore, $a_n = n \cdot a_{n-1}$.  Using this recursive formula, we can calculate $a_n$ for small values of $n$.  For $n=3$, $a_3 = 3 \cdot a_2 = 3 \cdot (2 \cdot a_1) = 3 \cdot (2 \cdot 1) = 6$.  For $n=4$, $a_4 = 4 \cdot a_3 = 4 \cdot

[Q]: Question: Если я хочу купить новую книгу, где можно сделать это? While books can also be found in other options such as a cabinet (B), an old house (C), a museum (D), or a library (E), these places aren't primarily meant for purchasing new books.

I have two tables one is users and other is user_details.  Users table:  id | name | email | password  User_details table:  id | user_id | phone | address  Now I want to get all users with their details.  How can I write this query in laravel eloquent?  A: You can use Eager Loading for this.  $users = User::with('user_details')->get();  In your User Model:  public function user_details()  {      return $this->hasOne(UserDetail::class, 'user_id');  }  In your UserDetail Model:  public function user()  {      return $this->belongsTo(User::class, 'user_id');  }  You can read more about Eager Loading here: https://laravel.com/docs/8.x/eloquent-relationships#eager-loading  A: You can use Relationships in Laravel Eloquent ORM. If you have been reading my previous blogs, you know that I am a big proponent of chiropractic care for children. There are so many benefits to getting your child adjusted regularly, but today I want to focus on just one of those benefits: ear infections.  Ear infections are incredibly common in children. According to the National Institute on Deafness and Other Communication Disorders (NIDCD), nearly all children will have had at least one ear infection by the time they turn three years old. That's a lot of kids with a lot of ear infections.  So what causes ear infections? Eustachian tubes connect the middle ear to the back of the nose. When these tubes become blocked, fluid can build up in the middle ear, leading to an infection. This blockage is often caused by allergies, colds, or other upper respiratory infections.  Symptoms of an ear infection include fever, fussiness, tugging or pulling at the ears, trouble sleeping, difficulty hearing, and fluid draining from the ear.  The most common treatment for ear infections is antibiotics. However, according to the American Academy of Pediatrics, more than half of all ear infections are caused by viruses,

Input:  English_Without_Tears  musicComposer  Nicholas_Brodszky ,  English_Without_Tears  director  Harold_French   Output:   The Pantanal is Brazil's largest wetland area and one of the world's most important conservation areas. It is home to many rare and endangered species, including jaguars, giant river otters, hyacinth macaws, and capybaras. In addition to its rich biodiversity, the Pantanal is also known for its unique landscape, which includes seasonally flooded grasslands, forests, and wetlands. This vast region spans over 195,000 square miles (505,000 square kilometers), encompassing parts of Brazil, Bolivia, and Paraguay. Due to its fragile ecosystem and environmental importance, the Pantanal was designated as a UNESCO World Heritage Site in 2000.

The Trade Finance Operations Guidance provides practical recommendations for banks and other financial institutions to facilitate trade finance transactions amidst the evolving challenges posed by the global health crisis. It outlines best practices for managing risks associated with physical document handling, remote working, cybersecurity, fraud prevention, and anti-money laundering and combating the financing of terrorism (AML/CFT) compliance.  The publication draws on the expertise of the ICC Banking Commission's Working Group on Trade Finance Operations, which includes representatives from leading financial institutions worldwide. It is designed to complement existing ICC guidance on trade finance operations, including the ICC Guide to Digital Trade Correspondent Banking and the ICC Guide to Digitisation of Documentary Credits. I am trying to create a list of lists where each inner list is sorted. For example, if I have this list:  my_list = [[3, 4, 1], [5, 2, 6], [9, 8, 7]]  The output should be:  [[1, 3, 4], [2, 5, 6], [7, 8, 9]]  Here is my code:  my_list = [[3, 4, 1], [5, 2, 6], [9, 8, 7]]  sorted_list = []  for sublist in my_list:      sublist.sort()      sorted_list.append(sublist)  print(sorted_list)  However, when I run this code, the output is the same as the input (my_list). Can someone explain why this is happening and how to fix it?  A: The problem with your code is that you are sorting the sublists in-place, which means that the changes made to the sublists are reflected in the original my_list variable.  To fix this, you can create a copy of the sublist before sorting it:  my_list = [[3, 4, 1

Input:  Big_Hero_6_(film)  distributor  Walt_Disney_Studios_Motion_Pictures ,  Baymax  series  Big_Hero_6_(film)   Output:   Q: Is there a way to get the value of a specific key in a list of dictionaries? I have a list of dictionaries which looks like this:  data = [{'name': 'John', 'age': 23, 'gender': 'M'}, {'name': 'Jane', 'age': 25, 'gender': 'F'}, {'name': 'Tom', 'age': 27, 'gender': 'M'}]  Is there a way to search for a specific name and return the age of that person? For example, if I want to search for "John" and return his age (23)?  A: You can use a list comprehension to filter the list of dictionaries based on the condition that the dictionary's 'name' key is equal to 'John'. Then, you can access the 'age' key of the filtered dictionary.  result = next((dictionary for dictionary in data if dictionary['name'] == 'John'), None)  if result:      age = result['age']  else:      age = None  print(age)  Output:  23  A: You can use a list comprehension to filter the list of dictionaries based on the condition that the dictionary's 'name' key is equal to 'John'. Then, you can access the 'age' key of the filtered dictionary

Input:  Ciudad_Ayala  populationDensity  1604.0 ,  Ciudad_Ayala  leaderTitle  Governator ,  Ciudad_Ayala  elevationAboveTheSeaLevel  1147.0 ,  Ciudad_Ayala  timeZone  Pacific_Daylight_Time ,  Ciudad_Ayala  timeZone  Pacific_Standard_Time_Zone   Output:   There is nothing quite like the smell of freshly baked bread wafting through the house. The process of kneading the dough, watching it rise, and seeing it transform into a golden-brown loaf is both satisfying and rewarding. But if you don't have the time or energy to make bread from scratch, store-bought bread might seem like the next best option. However, many store-bought breads contain ingredients that aren't ideal for our health or the environment. That's where sprouted grain bread comes in.  Sprouted grain bread is made from grains that have been soaked, germinated, and then ground into flour. This process makes the nutrients in the grains more bioavailable, meaning they are easier for our bodies to absorb and use. Sprouted grains are also lower in phytic acid, which can interfere with the absorption of essential minerals like calcium, magnesium, and iron.  In addition to being more nutritious, sprouted grain bread is also better for the environment. Traditional wheat processing involves removing the bran and germ during milling, which reduces the nutritional value of the flour. By using sprouted grains, we can make better use of the whole grain, reducing food waste and preserving the nutrients that would otherwise be discarded.  When choosing sprouted grain bread,

Registered nurses (RNs) provide and coordinate patient care, educate patients and the public about various health conditions, and provide emotional support and advice to patients' family members. They make judgments about patients' health and well-being, and may order and perform diagnostic tests when necessary. Registered nurses usually work in hospitals, physicians' offices, and long-term care facilities. Some RNs work in schools, rehabilitation centers, and home healthcare services. Most registered nurses work full time. Overtime and weekend work may be required.  Registered nurses typically need an associate's or bachelor's degree in nursing, although a diploma from an approved nursing program may suffice, and all state require licensure. Registered nurses must pass the National Council Licensure Examination (NCLEX-RN) to become licensed. Some states require or prefer that applicants for licensure graduate from an accredited nursing program. Nurses who want to advance to management positions may need a master's

"At this time, UHS has no evidence that any patient, physician or employee personal information has been accessed, copied or misused," the company said. "However, out of an abundance of caution, UHS will be notifying relevant regulators and individuals as required by applicable law." In this blog post, we will explore some of the top reasons why apples should be a regular part of your daily routine.  1. High in Fiber: Apples are an excellent source of dietary fiber, which is essential for maintaining healthy digestion. One medium-sized apple contains around 4.4 grams of fiber, which is approximately 17% of the recommended daily intake for adults.  2. Rich in Antioxidants: Apples contain high levels of antioxidants, particularly quercetin and catechin. These antioxidants help protect cells from damage caused by free radicals, reducing the risk of chronic diseases such as cancer and heart disease.  3. Promotes Heart Health: Studies have shown that consuming apples regularly can lower cholesterol levels and reduce the risk of developing heart disease. The soluble fiber in apples binds to cholesterol in the digestive tract, preventing it from being absorbed into the bloodstream.  4. Turing Award  ACM, in partnership with Google, is now accepting nominations for the 2023 A.M. Turing Award, generally recognized as the "Nobel Prize of Computing." The award, named after Alan M. Turing, carries a $1 million prize, with financial support provided by Google, and is presented annually to an individual selected for contributions of a technical nature made to the computing community. Nominations will be accepted until June 15, 2022.  The A.M. Turing Award is ACM's most prestigious honor and recognizes individuals whose research has had a lasting and profound impact on the innovation and creativity of the computer science and information technology fields. Established by ACM in 1966, the Turing Award is bestowed on an annual basis to an outstanding researcher in the field of computer science (or a closely related discipline) who demonstrates a commitment to the goals of the Association and whose contributions, in the estimation of the Turing Award Selection Committee, are of lasting and major technical importance to the field.  Candidates must have made fundamental contributions of lasting significance to the field of computer science. The contributions can be in theory, experimentation, or engineering; they may be in

I have two dataframes df1 and df2.  df1 looks like this:     A   B   C   D  0  1   2   3   4  1  5   6   7   8  2  9  10  11  12  And df2 looks like this:     E   F   G  0  1   2   3  1  4   5   6  2  7   8   9  I want to create a new dataframe called df3 which has all the columns from df1 and the corresponding values from df2.  So df3 will look like this:     A   B   C   D   E   F   G  0  1   2   3   4   1   2   3  1  5   6   7   8   4   5   6  2  9  10  11  12   7   8   9  How can I do this using pandas?  A: Use concat with join:  df3 = pd.concat([df1, df2], axis=1)  print (df3)     A  B  C  D  E  F  G  0  1  2  3  4  1  2  3

The purpose of this site is to provide information about our organization and its activities, and to promote communication among philosophers of religion around the world. Please feel free to explore the site, and to let us know if you have any comments or suggestions.  The IASPR was founded in 1986 by a group of philosophers of religion who met at the annual conference of the American Academy of Religion. Its primary aim is to facilitate communication among philosophers of religion around the world, and to promote the study of the philosophy of religion through conferences, publications, and other activities.  The IASPR holds international conferences every three years, bringing together philosophers of religion from around the world to present papers and discuss current issues in the field. The most recent conference was held in Krakow, Poland, in August 2018. The next conference will be held in Cape Town, South Africa, in August 2021.  The IASPR also publishes the Journal of the International Association of Philosophy of Religion (JIAPR), which appears twice a year. The JIAPR provides a forum for the publication of scholarly articles in the philosophy of religion, as well as book reviews and announcements of interest to philosophers of religion. Coffee Jr., Columbia Law School,Follow this and additional works at: https://scholarship.law.columbia.edu/faculty_scholarship/574  This Article explores the relationship between sovereign immunity and personal jurisdiction over foreign states. The Supreme Court's recent decision in Fed. Republic of Germany v. Philipp, 485 U.S. 438 (1988), held that the Eleventh Amendment does not preclude federal courts from exercising personal jurisdiction over foreign states. This conclusion is consistent with the Court's prior decisions holding that the Eleventh Amendment applies only to suits by citizens against their own state. However, the Philipp decision has been widely misinterpreted as endorsing the view that foreign states can be subjected to general personal jurisdiction in the United States. This Article argues that such an interpretation is inconsistent with the traditional principles governing personal jurisdiction over non-resident defendants. In particular, the Court's later decision in Asahi Metal Indus. Co. v. Superior Court, 480 U.S. 102 (1987), which was decided shortly after Philipp, suggests that foreign states should ordin

The advisory provides technical details on vulnerabilities commonly exploited by APT actors to gain initial access to these devices and recommends mitigations to reduce the risk of compromise.  "As cyber threats continue to evolve, CISA is committed to working with our interagency and private sector partners to provide timely and actionable information to help organizations secure their networks," said CISA Director Christopher C. Krebs. "This advisory serves as a reminder that all connected devices can be vulnerable to exploitation, and underscores the importance of implementing basic cyber hygiene best practices." Input:  ALCO_RS-3  buildDate  "May 1950 - August 1956" ,  ALCO_RS-3  length  17068.8 (millimetres)   Output:   Q: How do I create a user defined data type in SQL Server? I want to create a user defined data type in SQL Server. For example, I want to create a new data type named Fruit which will have values such as Apple, Orange, Banana, etc.  A: You can create a User Defined Table Type (UDT) in SQL Server. This allows you to define a structure for your data that can be used within stored procedures and functions. However, this is different from creating a new data type in the sense that you cannot use Fruit as a data type for a column in a table.  To create a UDT, follow these steps:  1. Open SQL Server Management Studio and connect to your database server.  2. Expand the Databases node and select the database where you want to create the UDT.  3. Right-click the Tables folder and select New Table...  4. In the New Table dialog box, specify a name for your UDT (e.g., dbo.Fruits).  5. Add columns to represent the attributes of your fruit objects. For example:  ```sql  CREATE TYPE dbo.Fruits AS TABLE (      FruitID INT IDENTITY(1,1) PRIMARY KEY,      FruitName VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,      Color VARCHAR(

Input:  Nie_Haisheng  mission  Shenzhou_10 ,  Nie_Haisheng  mission  Shenzhou_6 ,  Nie_Haisheng  birthDate  1964-10-13 ,  Nie_Haisheng  birthPlace  Zaoyang ,  Nie_Haisheng  birthPlace  Hubei   Output:   Home > News > featured news > Nuclear power plant operators can save money with new technology  Nuclear power plant operators can save money with new technology  energymonitor | March 25, 2019  A team of researchers at the U.S. Department of Energy's (DOE) Oak Ridge National Laboratory (ORNL) has developed a computer model that can predict corrosion rates for nuclear power plant heat exchangers. ORNL scientists have developed a first-of-its-kind computer model that can predict corrosion rates for nuclear power plant heat exchangers. The tool will help plant operators better understand how their equipment is aging and when repairs or replacements are needed, potentially saving millions of dollars in maintenance costs. Heat exchangers transfer heat between two fluids that do not come into direct contact with each other. In a nuclear power plant, they are used to cool the reactor core and convert steam back into water. Over time, the heat exchangers can corrode, which decreases their efficiency and could lead to premature failure. Understanding the rate of corrosion is critical to maintaining the safety and reliability of the plant. Plant operators currently monitor corrosion by removing small pieces of the heat exchanger tubes for analysis. This process is expensive, time-consuming, and disrupts plant operations. "This approach only provides a snapshot of the

The victim was a 48-year-old man from Zhejiang province in eastern China, who died on Dec 15, the official Xinhua news agency said.  He had visited a live poultry market before falling ill with symptoms including fever, coughing and chest tightness, Xinhua said.  The H7N9 strain of bird flu first appeared in humans in China in 2013 and led to more than 1,000 deaths over the following five years.  Since 2017, however, there have only been sporadic cases, according to the World Health Organisation (WHO).  The WHO says the risk of human-to-human transmission of H7N9 is considered low. The solution will be made available to vehicle manufacturers and parking lot operators globally through Baidu Apollo's open platform.  Baidu Apollo's AVP solution consists of hardware, software, and cloud services. It leverages Baidu Apollo's proprietary HD maps, high-precision localization technology, and deep learning-based perception algorithms to enable vehicles to navigate complex urban environments and accurately locate parking spots. The solution also integrates with existing parking infrastructure such as traffic lights, gates, and barriers to facilitate seamless communication between vehicles and parking facilities. Please note that these dates do not represent the dates on which the women died, but rather the dates on which their bodies were discovered. A: You can use itertools.combinations:  from itertools import combinations  data = [(1, 5), (2, 6), (3, 7), (4, 8)]  result = list(map(list, combinations(map(list, data), 2)))  print(result)  Prints:  [(-1, 1), (-1, 2), (-1, 3), (-1, 4), (1, 2), (1, 3), (1, 4), (2, 3), (2, 4), (3, 4)]  A: You can use itertools.combinations with list comprehension:  from itertools import combinations  data = [(1, 5),

Despite having a successful career as a lawyer and a loving family, she can't shake off the nagging feeling that there's something more out there for her.  One day, while cleaning out her late grandmother's attic, Emma stumbles upon an old, mysterious painting. Intrigued by its beauty and the sense of familiarity it evokes, she decides to have it restored. During the restoration process, Emma learns that the painting is a portrait of her great-great-grandmother, painted by a renowned artist just before he mysteriously vanished.  Eager to uncover the truth behind the artist's disappearance, Emma embarks on a journey that takes her across Europe. Along the way, she meets other descendants of the artist's muses, all of whom have been searching for answers in their own lives. Democrats hold a supermajority in both houses of the Legislature, but they need two-thirds support to pass a budget or raise taxes. But Assemblyman Sam Blakeslee, a moderate Republican from San Luis Obispo, said his party was united against the tax increase.  “There’s no question that our caucus is solidly opposed to it,” Mr. Blakeslee said.  The measure would have raised the state sales tax by 1 percentage point, to 8.25 percent, and increased income taxes on individuals making more than $250,000 a year and couples making more than $500,000. It would have generated about $12 billion over the next 18 months.

Input:  Brandon_Carter  doctoralAdvisor  Dennis_William_Sciama ,  Brandon_Carter  birthDate  1942-01-01 ,  Brandon_Carter  birthPlace  England   Output:   Q: Why do we need to define the type explicitly when using generics? I have been reading about generics in C# and I am having trouble understanding why we need to explicitly define the type for the generic class.  For example:  Dictionary<string, string> myDictionary = new Dictionary<string, string>();  Why can't we just do this:  Dictionary myDictionary = new Dictionary();  Also, what is the difference between these two lines of code:  Dictionary<string, string> myDictionary = new Dictionary<string, string>();  Dictionary<string> myDictionary = new Dictionary<string, string>();  A: The first line creates a dictionary with keys and values of type string.  The second line creates a dictionary with keys of type string and values of type object.  In order to know which type to use for the key and value, the compiler needs to know both types.  Without specifying the types, the compiler wouldn't know which type to use for the key and which type to use for the value.  This could lead to unexpected behavior if you tried to use the dictionary in a way that depends on the types of the key and value.  A: As others have said, because without specifying the types, the compiler doesn't know which type to use for the key and which type to use for the value.  As far as your second question goes, let'

UBS Financial Services Inc. has agreed to pay more than $6 million to settle charges by the Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC) that it failed to supervise its brokers for excessive mutual fund trading, known as churning.  According to the SEC's order, between 2009 and 2013, UBS received numerous red flags indicating that certain brokers were excessively trading mutual fund shares in their customers' accounts. Despite these red flags, UBS failed to implement reasonable supervisory procedures to detect and prevent excessive trading. The firm also failed to adequately train its branch managers to identify and address excessive trading.  The SEC's order finds that UBS caused violations of Section 206(4) of the Investment Advisers Act of 1940 and Rule 206(4)-7 thereunder, which impose a duty on investment advisers to adopt and implement written policies and procedures reasonably designed to prevent violations of

The Guide to Bank-Customer Relationship Management is designed to assist banks in implementing robust customer relationship management frameworks. It provides guidance on how banks can meet their obligations to customers, regulators and other stakeholders, while also managing reputational risks.  "This guide aims to help banks achieve excellence in customer relationship management, which is critical to maintaining trust in the banking system," said Marcus Hughes, Chair of the ICC Banking Commission. The guide outlines the components of a sound customer relationship management framework, including governance, risk management, policies and procedures, training and communications. It also includes case studies illustrating good practices implemented by banks around the world. Input:  Andrzej_Piotr_Ruszczyński  professionalField  Mathematical_optimization   Output:   It's been quite some time since I last posted here, but I've been busy with work and other things. Now that we're getting closer to the end of the year, I wanted to write about one of my favorite subjects: The weather.  In particular, I want to talk about temperature and precipitation trends over the past few decades in the United States. We know that globally, temperatures have risen and extreme weather events have become more frequent, but what does this mean for us here in the U.S.?  According to data from the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration (NOAA), the average annual temperature in the contiguous United States has increased by about 1.6°F (0.9°C) since record-keeping began in 1895. This may not sound like much, but it's important to note that most of this warming has occurred since the 1970s. In fact, the decade from 2010 to 2019 was the warmest on record for the U.S., with an average temperature of 54.3°F (12.4°C).  As for precipitation, the picture is a bit more complex. Overall, the U.S. has seen an increase in precipitation since the late 19th century, with an average increase of about 4% per century

Teaching School Alliance  Schools Direct Programme  SCITT Programme  NQT Programme  Newly Qualified Teacher (NQT) Programme  The Newly Qualified Teacher (NQT) Programme is designed to support NQTs in their first year of teaching. The programme supports NQTs to develop as reflective practitioners who are able to meet the requirements of the Teachers' Standards.  The NQT Programme is delivered through a partnership between the TSA and the employing school. The NQT will be assigned a Professional Mentor within their employing school, who will work alongside the TSA mentor to support the NQT throughout the year.  The NQT Programme consists of four elements:  Induction Sessions  All NQTs will attend two induction sessions during the academic year. These sessions will provide opportunities for NQTs to network with other NQTs, share good practice and engage in professional development.  Mentoring Support  Each NQT will be allocated a TSA mentor and a Professional Mentor within their employing school. The TSA mentor will meet with the NQT at least three times during the academic year

I tried using the epsilon-delta definition of continuity, but I couldn't figure out how to show that for every $\epsilon > 0$, there exists a $\delta > 0$ such that $|f'(x) - f'(c)| < \epsilon$ whenever $|x - c| < \delta$.  Any hints or solutions would be appreciated.  A: Since $f$ is differentiable on $(a,b)$, we know that for each $x$ in $(a,b)$, there exists a $\delta_x>0$ such that $|f(x+h)-f(x)-f'(x)h|<\epsilon$ for all $0<|h|<\delta_x$.  Let $c\in [a,b]$. If $c\in (a,b)$, then take $\delta=\delta_c$.  If $c=a$ or $c=b$, then choose $\delta>0$ such that $c+\delta$ or $c-\delta$ is in $(a,b)$.  In both cases, we have $|f(x+h)-f(x)-f'(x)h|<\epsilon$ for all $0<

I have two pages named Page1.aspx and Page2.aspx. In Page1.aspx, I have a textbox and a button. On clicking the button, I want to pass the value entered in the textbox to Page2.aspx. How can I do this?  A: You can use QueryString for passing data between pages.  In Page1.aspx, when you click the button :  Response.Redirect("Page2.aspx?textBoxValue=" + TextBox1.Text);  In Page2.aspx, you can retrieve the value using Request.QueryString["textBoxValue"]  A: There are several ways to do this.   *  *You can store the value in Session object and access it in the next page.  *You can pass the value through querystring parameters.  *You can create a hidden field in the second page and set its value before redirecting to the second page.  A: You could use TempData which is stored only for the duration of the next request. This means that after the next request has been completed, the data is discarded.  In Page1.aspx:  TempData["textBoxValue"] = TextBox1.Text;  return RedirectToAction

This voluntary framework provides a common language for communicating cybersecurity risks and serves as a blueprint for organizations to manage and reduce those risks.  The updated Framework reflects changes in technology, cyber threats, and industry practices since the publication of the original Framework in 2014. In 1894 Wood went to the Wagner festival at Bayreuth where he met the conductor Felix Mottl, who subsequently appointed him as his assistant and chorus master for a series of Wagner concerts at the newly built Queen's Hall in London. The manager of the hall, Robert Newman, was proposing to run a ten-week season of promenade concerts and, impressed by Wood, invited him to conduct. There had been such concerts in London since 1838, under conductors from Louis Antoine Jullien to Arthur Sullivan. Sullivan's concerts in the 1870s had been particularly successful, because he attracted large audiences by offering something more than the usual light music. He introduced major classical works, occasionally for orchestra alone and occasionally with soloists or chorus, but always including lively items to appeal to all sections of the audience. It is in this category of popular classical concerts that the promenade concerts of Wood's time may be placed, and their success is due in large part to Wood's following in Sullivan's footsteps.At the opening concert on 10 July

Input:  It's_Great_to_Be_Young_(1956_film)  starring  John_Mills ,  It's_Great_to_Be_Young_(1956_film)  cinematography  Gilbert_Taylor ,  It's_Great_to_Be_Young_(1956_film)  runtime  94.0 ,  It's_Great_to_Be_Young_(1956_film)  gross  282838.0 ,  It's_Great_to_Be_Young_(1956_film)  musicComposer  Louis_Levy   Output:   Q: Why does this function return undefined? I am learning javascript and I wrote this simple function to check if a string contains a given substring. The function returns undefined instead of true or false. Can someone explain why?  let hasSubstring = function(string, substring) {    if (string.indexOf(substring) !== -1) {      return true;    } else {      return false;    }  };  console.log(hasSubstring("test", "es"));  A: This is because indexOf returns -1 when the substring isn't found.  Change your code to:  let hasSubstring = function(string, substring) {    if (string.indexOf(substring) != -1) {      return true;    } else {      return false;    }  };  A: The indexOf() method returns -1 when the specified value is not present in the string.  So, you need to compare with != -1 instead of !== -1.  let hasSubstring = function(string, substring) {    if (string.indexOf(substring) != -1) {      return true;    } else {      return false;    }  };  console.log(hasSubstring("test", "es"));

Input:  English_Without_Tears  writer  Terence_Rattigan ,  Terence_Rattigan  birthDate  1911-01-01   Output:   Home / News / Business & Economy / Minneapolis Fed chief urges Congress to act on small business aid  Minneapolis Federal Reserve Bank President Neel Kashkari speaks during a news conference in Minneapolis in this file photo. Kashkari is urging Congress to pass legislation providing more help for small businesses hurt by the coronavirus pandemic. (AP Photo/Jim Mone, File)  Minneapolis Fed chief urges Congress to act on small business aid  By: The Associated Press September 23, 2020 4:57 pm  MINNEAPOLIS — The head of the Federal Reserve Bank of Minneapolis is urging Congress to pass legislation providing more help for small businesses hurt by the coronavirus pandemic.  Neel Kashkari, president of the Minneapolis Fed, said in a statement released Wednesday that "small businesses are facing an existential threat."  He urged Congress to pass another round of funding for the Paycheck Protection Program, which provides forgivable loans to small businesses to help them keep workers on their payrolls.  Kashkari also called for additional funding for the Economic Injury Disaster Loan program, which provides low-interest loans to small businesses affected by the pandemic.  "Small businesses are the backbone of our economy," Kashkari said. "If they fail, we all suffer."  Like this article

Other causes of low back pain include degenerative disc disease, spinal stenosis, sciatica, and spondylolisthesis. Treatment for low back pain typically involves rest, ice or heat therapy, anti-inflammatory medications, and physical therapy. In some cases, more aggressive treatments such as epidural steroid injections or surgery may be necessary. It is important to consult with a healthcare professional for an accurate diagnosis and personalized treatment plan.

Academic journal article Journal of Marriage and Family  Parenting Practices and Adolescent Well-Being: A Comparison of Two Cohorts  By McLoyd, Vonnie M.; Duarte, Tiffany L.; Peterson, Glen H.  This study examined trends in parenting practices and their relation to adolescent well-being over a 20-year period. Using data from two waves of the National Longitudinal Study of Adolescent Health (Add Health), we investigated whether changes in parenting practices were associated with changes in adolescent self-esteem, depressive symptoms, and delinquent behavior among African American and European American adolescents. Results showed that parents became more involved in their adolescents' lives between Wave I (1994-1995) and Wave II (2001-2002). Parental monitoring increased for both African American and European American adolescents, whereas parental warmth increased only for European American adolescents. Changes in parenting practices were associated with changes in adolescent well-being. Specifically, increases in parental warmth and monitoring were associated with decreases in depressive symptoms

I have a string like this:  my_string = "Hello World!"  And I want to change the color of the letter 'o' in the word 'World' to green.  How can I do this in Python?  A: To change the color of a specific character in a string in Python, you need to use terminal escape sequences and output the result to a terminal supporting ANSI/VT100 color codes. Here is an example using the termcolor library:  from termcolor import cprint  my_string = "Hello World!"  change_char = 'o'  change_index = my_string.find('World')  new_string = my_string[0:change_index] + '\033[32m' + change_char + '\033[0m' + my_string[change_index+5:]  cprint(new_string)  In this example, we use the termcolor library to print colored text. We find the index of the substring 'World' in the original string, then create a new string by replacing the character we want to change with the ANSI escape sequence for green text, followed by the character, followed by the reset sequence. Finally, we use the cprint function from the termcolor library to print the

Example:  list1 = ["a", "b", "c"]  list2 = [1, 2, 3]  function(list1, list2) #should return -1 because there is no match  list1 = ["a", "b", "c"]  list2 = [1, 2, 3, "a"]  function(list1, list2) #should return 3 because 'a' is present at index 3 in list2  A: You can use itertools.zip_longest to zip the two lists together, checking if the value exists in the other list using set intersection, and returning the index of the first True value:  from itertools import zip_longest  def find_match(lst1, lst2):      for i, (x, y) in enumerate(zip_longest(lst1, lst2, fillvalue=None)):          if x is not None and set([x]).intersection(lst2):              return

I am trying to make a program that calculates the sum of all the digits in a number entered by the user. The condition is that the number should be greater than 999 and less than 9999. How can I do this using a for loop?  A: You can use a while loop instead of a for loop:  n = int(input("Enter a number: "))  while n <= 999 or n >= 9999:      print("Please enter a number between 1000 and 9999")      n = int(input("Enter a number: "))  sum_of_digits = sum(map(int, str(n)))  print(f"The sum of digits of {n} is {sum_of_digits}")  A: You can use a while loop instead of a for loop to check if the number entered by the user satisfies the given condition. Bio: william fife knowland -lrb- august 31 , 1908 -- march 23 , 1974 -rrb- was an american publisher and republican politician from california . he was president of the `` oakland tribune '' from 1933 to 1945 and president of the international news service from 1945 to 1951 . in 1951 he was appointed to the united states senate following the death of his father , u.s. senator frank barrett knowland , to fill the seat until a replacement was elected . knowland himself was then elected to a full term , serving from 1953 to 1959 . he was minority leader for two years , 1957 to 1959 . in 1959 , knowland ran for governor of california but lost the republican primary to richard nixon , who went on to defeat sergeant shriver in the general election . knowland later served as chairman of the republican national committee from 1962 to 1964 during the tenure of president john f. kennedy and president lyndon b. johnson .

Input:  Mexico  leader  Roberto_Gil_Zuarth   Output:   Home » Browse » Academic journals » General Social Science Journals » Journal of Marriage and Family » Article details, "The Influence of Parental Divorce on Children's..."  Academic journal article Journal of Marriage and Family  The Influence of Parental Divorce on Children's Educational Attainment: The Role of Parenting Behaviors  By Hetherington, E. Mavis; Cox, Melissa; Cox, Matthew  Using data from the National Longitudinal Study of Adolescent Health (Add Health), this study investigates the mechanisms through which parental divorce influences children's educational attainment. We examine the role of parenting behaviors-parental monitoring, parental involvement, and parental support-as mediators of the association between parental divorce and children's educational attainment. Our findings indicate that parenting behaviors play a significant role in explaining the relationship between parental divorce and children's educational attainment. More specifically, we found that the negative effects of parental divorce on children's educational attainment were largely accounted for by lower levels of parental monitoring, parental involvement, and parental support. These findings suggest that interventions aimed at promoting positive parenting behaviors among divorced parents could potentially offset some of the negative effects of divorce on children's educational attainment.  Parental divorce has become increasingly common

The city of Rome was the largest city in the world BC AD, with Constantinople (New Rome) becoming the largest around 500 AD, and the Empire's populace grew to an estimated 50 to 90 million inhabitants. The 500-year-old republic which preceded it was severely destabilized in a series of civil wars and political conflict, during which Julius Caesar was appointed as perpetual dictator and then assassinated in 44 BC. Caesar's adopted heir Augustus established the Empire as a one-man rule with himself as Emperor after defeating Caesar's killers in the Civil War of 43 to 31 BC, bringing to an end the Republican period.  - In historiography, the Western Roman Empire consists of the western provinces of the Roman Empire at any one time during which they were administered by a separate and independent Imperial court, co-existent with but both independent of and parallel to that administering the Eastern Roman Empire (or Byzantine Empire). If you know David Darnell's email, phone number, or address, please click here to update their listing.  What is the difference between "it's" and "its"?  The apostrophe indicates possession when used with singular nouns. For example, "It's book" shows that the book belongs to 'it'. On the other hand, 'its' is used for both singular and plural nouns to indicate possession. For example, "The dog ran with its ball". In this case, 'its' is used for the singular noun 'dog'.

Academic journal article Studies in Romanticism  Coleridge's Biographical Criticism: The Case of Milton  By Shapiro, Alan  Samuel Taylor Coleridge's biography of John Milton (1817) has been recognized as a landmark in the history of literary biography, but its status as a work of literary criticism has received less attention. This essay examines Coleridge's reading of Milton's poetry in his biography, focusing on how Coleridge's biographical method is used to elucidate Milton's poetic art. In particular, this essay shows how Coleridge's biographical account of Milton's life and thought serves to enhance our understanding of Paradise Lost. Coleridge's biography demonstrates how the author's life can be used to illuminate the meaning of a literary text, but it also reveals some of the limitations of this approach. Specifically, the study examined the impact of CSR on return on assets (ROA), return on equity (ROE) and earnings per share (EPS) of firms listed on the NSE. The study adopted secondary data sourced from the annual reports and accounts of selected firms for the period 2009-2013. Actually, the ice age, which began about two million years ago, has been through several periods of melting and refreezing. The most recent period of melting lasted from about 11,000 B.C. to 7,000 B.C. In other words, it lasted for 4,000 years. We call this period the last Ice Age. Within the last Ice Age, the sea level rose about 300 feet. However, sea level did not rise at a constant rate. It is true that glaciers are a major form of ice on the earth, but they cover only 10 percent of its total surface; the rest is land ice and polar ice caps . While the amount of glaciers decreases, the amount of land ice from Greenland and the polar regions actually increases. Scientific research shows that even if all the glaciers and polar ice caps melt completely, the sea level will rise only about 75 feet. But I can use this background: In exercises such as weight lifting, skeletal muscles are contracted against a resisting force (see Figure below ). Using skeletal muscle in this way increases its size and strength. In exercises such as running, the cardiac muscle contracts faster and the heart pumps more blood. Using cardiac muscle in this way increases its strength and efficiency. Continued exercise is necessary to maintain bigger, stronger muscles. If you don’t use a muscle, it will get smaller and weaker—so use it or lose it.  What is an answer for this question: Which group's cardiac muscle will not be more efficient?  Answer:  Group A

The bodies of seven of the eight people still missing have been located by drones and helicopters, but rescuers have been unable to recover them due to continuing hazardous conditions.  Prime Minister Jacinda Ardern said earlier this week she was "very open" to sending a military team to recover the bodies, but only if it was safe to do so. Input:  Olga_Bondareva  birthDate  1937-04-27 ,  Olga_Bondareva  professionalField  Mathematics ,  Olga_Bondareva  professionalField  Economics   Output:   The U.S. Food and Drug Administration (FDA) has approved Gilead Sciences' Truvada (emtricitabine and tenofovir disoproxil fumarate) for pre-exposure prophylaxis (PrEP) to reduce the risk of sexually acquired HIV-1 infection in at-risk adults.  Truvada is the first drug approved by the FDA for this indication, which involves taking antiretroviral drugs to prevent HIV infection in people who do not have the virus but are at high risk of acquiring it through sexual activity.  The approval was based on data from two Phase III clinical trials, iPrEx and Partners PrEP, which showed that daily use of Truvada reduced the risk of HIV-1 infection by approximately 44% and 75%, respectively.  In the iPrEX study, men who have sex with men and transgender individuals were randomized to receive either Truvada or placebo once daily. At week 48, the incidence of HIV-1 infection was significantly lower in the Truvada group than in the placebo group (1.3% vs. 3.4%).  In the Partners PrEP study, heterosexual serodiscordant couples (in which one partner is HIV-positive and the other is HIV-negative) were randomized to receive either Tru

This is the first finding of HPAI in a commercial turkey flock in Iowa since March 2016. USDA's National Veterinary Services Laboratories (NVSL) in Ames, Iowa, confirmed the findings.  On January 18, 2019, the Iowa State Veterinarian's office received a report of increased mortality and respiratory signs in a commercial turkey flock in Dubuque County. On January 19, 2019, the Iowa State Veterinarian's office confirmed the presence of HPAI in the flock. APHIS is working closely with the Iowa Department of Agriculture and Land Stewardship on a joint incident response. State officials quarantined the premises and depopulation of the flock is underway. Birds on the affected premises will be humanely euthanized and properly disposed of. APHIS will conduct surveillance within a 6-mile radius of the affected premises. Input:  Super_Capers  language  English_language   Output:   Q: How to set up multiple domain names for one website? I have a website which is currently only available at www.example.com.  I want to make it also available at www.example2.com.  How can I do this?  A: You need to configure your DNS server to map example2.com to the same IP address as example.com.  You could also use CNAME records to map example2.com to example.com.  If you don't have access to your DNS server, you will need to contact your hosting provider.  A: You need to change the DNS settings for example2.com to point to the same IP address as example.com.  This can usually be done through your domain registrar (the company you registered example2.com with) or by contacting your web host if they manage your DNS settings.  You can either create an A record for example2.com with the same IP address as the A record for example.com, or you can create a CNAME record for example2.com that points to example.com.  After making these changes, it can take up to 48 hours for the changes to propagate across the internet.

A: To get the last day of the previous month, you can use the following code:  const today = moment();  const lastDayOfPrevMonth = moment(today).subtract('month', 1).endOf('month');  console.log(lastDayOfPrevMonth);  <script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/moment.js/2.29.1/moment.min.js"></script>  Explanation:  *  *First, we define today's date using moment().  *Then, we subtract one month from today using the subtract() method.  *Finally, we use the endOf('month') method to get the last day of the resulting month.  This will give us the last day of the previous month regardless of the current date. Here is an example:  #!/bin/bash  string="abc"  file="/path/to/file"  if grep -q "$string" "$file"; then      echo "String found"  else      echo "String not found"  fi  When I run this script, it always outputs "String not found", even if the string "abc" is present in the file. Input:  English_Without_Tears  producer  Anatole_de_Grunwald ,  English_Without_Tears  writer  Anatole_de_Grunwald ,  English_Without_Tears  cinematography  Bernard_Knowles   Output:   Q: How to create multiple instances of a class? I am trying to create multiple instances of a class in order to use them in a for loop.  Here is my code:  class MyClass:      def __init__(self, value):          self.value = value      def print_value(self):          print(self.value)  list_of_values = [1, 2, 3]  for value in list_of_values:      instance = MyClass(value)      instance.print_value()  The problem is that when I run this code, it only prints the last value of the list (in this case, 3).  How can I create multiple instances of MyClass so that each instance has its own value and I can print all the values in the for loop?  A: The issue here is that you're creating a new instance of MyClass in every iteration of the loop, but you're only calling the print_value method on the last instance created.  To fix this, you could move the call to print_value inside the loop:  class MyClass:      def __init__(self, value):          self.value = value      def print_value(self):          print(self.value)  list_of_values = [1, 2, 3]

Input:  Adolfo_Suárez_Madrid–Barajas_Airport  operatingOrganisation  ENAIRE ,  ENAIRE  city  Madrid ,  Adolfo_Suárez_Madrid–Barajas_Airport  runwayLength  3500.0 ,  Adolfo_Suárez_Madrid–Barajas_Airport  elevationAboveTheSeaLevel  610.0   Output:   Q: How to set up two-way synchronization between two SQL Server databases I have two SQL Server databases (let's call them A and B) with the same structure. Database A is the main database and its data needs to be replicated to Database B. At the same time, changes made in Database B need to be propagated back to Database A. In other words, both databases need to stay in sync at all times.  How can I achieve this two-way synchronization between these two databases?  A: There are several ways to do this, depending on your requirements.  *  *SQL Server Replication - This is built-in feature in SQL Server that allows you to create publication and subscriptions between two databases. You can configure it for two-way synchronization.  *Change Data Capture (CDC) - You can use CDC to capture changes in one database and then apply those changes to the other database using a job or trigger.  *Transactional Replication with Snapshot Agent - You can use transactional replication to push changes from one database to another. But instead of using log reader agent, you can use snapshot agent to take a snapshot of the publishing database and apply it to the subscriber database. Then you can use CDC or triggers to capture changes in the subscriber database and push them back to the publisher database.

I have installed Git for Windows (from https://git-scm.com/download/win) and I want to use Git Bash instead of CMD.  How do I set up my .gitconfig so that I can use Git Bash without having to type git bash every time?  A: There is no need to change anything in your .gitconfig.  To make Git Bash your default console, follow these steps:  *  *Open Control Panel > System > Advanced system settings  *Click Environment Variables  *In the System variables section, find Path and select Edit  *Add the path to the Git Bash executable at the beginning of the list  *Restart your computer  Now, when you press Windows + R to open the Run dialog, the default console will be Git Bash.  A: The other answers here show how to make Git Bash your default command prompt. However, if you just want to run Git Bash without having to type git bash every time, you can create a shortcut to Git Bash on your desktop or taskbar.  *  *Open File Explorer and navigate to C:\Program Files\Git\bin  *Right-click on bash.

Input:  Nord_(Year_of_No_Light_album)  genre  Post-metal   Output:   Q: How to display data from multiple tables? I have two tables named "employee" and "salary". The employee table has columns emp_id, name, designation, and salary table has columns emp_id, basic_salary, da, hra, and total_salary.  I want to display all the data from the employee table along with their respective basic_salary, da, hra, and total_salary from the salary table.  How can I do this using MySQL?  A: You can use JOIN statement to combine data from multiple tables.  SELECT e.emp_id, e.name, e.designation, s.basic_salary, s.da, s.hra, s.total_salary  FROM employee AS e  INNER JOIN salary AS s  ON e.emp_id = s.emp_id  This query will join the employee table (aliased as e) with the salary table (aliased as s) using the common emp_id column. The result will contain all the columns specified in the SELECT clause for each row where there is a matching emp_id between the two tables.

Subtract 6 from both sides of the equation:     -15 - 6 = 3*b + 6 - 6     -21 = 3*b  2. Divide both sides by 3 to isolate b:     -21 / 3 = 3*b / 3     -7 = b  So, the value of b is -7.The answer is: -7

Input:  Super_Capers  distributor  Roadside_Attractions ,  Lionsgate  service  Digital_distribution ,  Super_Capers  distributor  Lionsgate ,  Lionsgate  service  Broadcast_programming   Output:   Q: How do I create a list of tuples from a list of lists? I have a list of lists like this:  [[1,2],[3,4],[5,6]]  And I want to transform it into a list of tuples like this:  [(1,2),(3,4),(5,6)]  Can anyone help me with this?  A: Use a list comprehension:  my_list = [[1,2],[3,4],[5,6]]  my_tuple_list = [tuple(x) for x in my_list]  print(my_tuple_list)  Output:  [(1, 2), (3, 4), (5, 6)]  A: You can use a list comprehension:  my_list = [[1,2],[3,4],[5,6]]  my_tuple_list = [tuple(sublist) for sublist in my_list]  print(my_tuple_list)  Output:  [(1, 2), (3, 4), (5, 6)]  A: Using map() function:  my_list = [[1,2],[3,4],[5,6]]  my_tuple_list = list(map(tuple, my_list))

The research, published in the journal Drug and Alcohol Dependence, shows that adolescents who consume energy drinks are also more likely to engage in other risky behaviors, such as hazardous drinking, cigarette smoking, marijuana use, and illicit drug use.  "Energy drinks have become increasingly popular among adolescents over the past decade," said lead investigator Dr. Brian A. Primack, associate professor of medicine at the University of Pittsburgh School of Medicine and director of the Center for Research on Media, Technology, and Health at UPMC.  "This study suggests that energy drinks may serve as a gateway to other unhealthy behaviors."  For the study, researchers analyzed data from the 2011-2014 National Youth Risk Behavior Surveys, which included self-reported information from more than 75,000 adolescents in grades 9 through 12 across the United States. Write a script to solve this quadratic equation.  A: To solve the equation -13*m + 11*m = 0 for m, we can combine the terms on the left side:  (-13 + 11) * m = 0  -2 * m = 0  Now, to isolate m, we divide both sides of the equation by -2:  (-2 * m) / (-2) = 0 / (-2)  m = 0  So, the solution to the quadratic equation is m = 0.

This innovative heating panel combines both radiant and convective heat into one single unit.  Radiant heat warms objects and people directly, whereas convective heat warms the air which then heats the objects and people within the room.  The Dual-Wave™ Infrared Heating Panel can be used in place of traditional radiators for whole room heating, or as a supplementary heat source to reduce energy consumption.  The Dual-Wave™ Infrared Heating Panel uses carbon fibre heating elements to produce long wave infrared heat. This type of heat is similar to the warmth we feel from the sun, gently warming objects and people without drying out the air.  A built-in fan blows warm air through ventilation slots along the bottom edge of the panel, distributing the heat evenly throughout the room.  The Dual-Wave™ Infrared Heating Panel has a sleek, minimalist design with a choice of finishes to suit any interior. Input:  Max_Benedict  deathPlace  London   Output:   Home » News » India » 'Covid-19 Vaccine Won't End Pandemic Completely': WHO Chief Scientist  'Covid-19 Vaccine Won't End Pandemic Completely': WHO Chief Scientist  By: News Desk  Edited By: Aakarshuk Sengupta  Last Updated: November 24, 2020, 16:57 IST  WHO chief scientist Soumya Swaminathan (File photo)  Swaminathan also said that there is no evidence to suggest that the vaccines will prevent transmission of the virus.  The Covid-19 vaccine will not end the pandemic completely, World Health Organisation (WHO) chief scientist Soumya Swaminathan said on Tuesday.  Speaking at a media briefing, Swaminathan also said that there is no evidence to suggest that the vaccines will prevent transmission of the virus.  "Vaccines will allow us to decrease mortality and severe disease, but they will not take us to zero transmission," Swaminathan said.  She further said that masks, hand hygiene, physical distancing and avoiding crowded spaces will continue to be important even after the vaccination drive begins.  "We need to keep doing all these things because we don't know yet whether the vaccines will prevent transmission or not," she added.

Input:  It's_Great_to_Be_Young_(1956_film)  director  Cyril_Frankel ,  Cyril_Frankel  birthPlace  United_Kingdom   Output:   Home » News » Blog » The Future of Electric Vehicles  The Future of Electric Vehicles  July 28, 2021 | Blog, News  Electric vehicles (EVs) have been around for over a century, but only in recent years have they started to gain widespread popularity. According to the International Energy Agency (IEA), global sales of electric cars increased by 41% in 2020 despite the economic disruption caused by the COVID-19 pandemic.  In this article, we'll take a closer look at the current state of electric vehicles and what the future might hold for this growing industry.  What is an Electric Vehicle?  An electric vehicle (EV) is a vehicle that uses electricity as its primary source of power. There are three main types of EVs: battery electric vehicles (BEVs), plug-in hybrid electric vehicles (PHEVs), and hybrid electric vehicles (HEVs).  BEVs, also known as all-electric vehicles, are powered solely by electricity stored in rechargeable batteries. PHEVs have both an internal combustion engine (ICE) and an electric motor powered by a rechargeable battery. HEVs also have an ICE and an electric motor, but the battery is charged through regenerative braking rather than being plugged into an external power source.  Current State of Electric Vehicles

It's hard to argue with that sentiment. As long as there are people who want to engage in certain behaviors, whether it's sex work, drug use, or something else, there will always be a demand for those activities. Attempting to ban or criminalize these behaviors rarely results in their complete eradication; instead, it often leads to negative consequences such as pushing these activities into the shadows, where they can become more dangerous and exploitative.  A more effective approach might be to focus on harm reduction and regulation. This means creating legal frameworks and social norms that allow individuals to engage in these behaviors in a safer and more controlled manner. For example, in the case of sex work, decriminalization can lead to improved health and safety outcomes for sex workers by allowing them to report abuse and access support services without fear of prosecution. Similarly, evidence suggests that regulated drug consumption sites can reduce overdose deaths, HIV transmission, and other harms associated with drug use.  Regulation doesn't necessarily mean endorsing or encouraging these behaviors. Instead, it acknowledges that they exist and aims to mitigate the risks and negative consequences associated with them. By doing so, we can better protect the rights

Nightmares are common in children, particularly between the ages of 3 and 6 years. They often reflect fears and anxieties that the child is experiencing during the day. For example, a child who is scared of the dark may have nightmares about being chased by a monster.  There are several things you can do to help your child cope with nightmares. Firstly, reassure your child that the dream was not real and that they are safe. Encourage them to talk about their dream and try to understand what might have triggered it. This could involve discussing any worries or fears they have during the day.  Develop a bedtime routine that helps your child relax and wind down before going to sleep. This could include a warm bath, reading a book, or listening to calming music. Make sure the bedroom is comfortable, dark, and quiet.  Encourage your child to express their feelings and concerns during the day through play, art, or conversation. This can help them work through any issues that may be causing nightmares.  If nightmares continue to be a frequent issue for your child, consider speaking with a mental health professional for additional guidance and support.

The deal is aimed at strengthening Apple's on-device machine learning capabilities, which will allow iPhones and iPads to process data locally without having to send it to the cloud.  Xnor.ai was founded in 2017 by five researchers from the University of Washington who specialised in computer vision and machine learning. The company developed low-power AI technology that can run on devices with limited processing power, such as cameras, wearables, and other Internet of Things (IoT) devices.  The acquisition gives Apple access to Xnor.ai's expertise in edge computing, which refers to the processing of data close to where it is generated, rather than sending it to a central server or data centre. This approach offers several benefits, including faster processing times, improved security, and reduced reliance on network connectivity

Input:  Darinka_Dentcheva  almaMater  Humboldt_University ,  Darinka_Dentcheva  residence  New_Jersey ,  Darinka_Dentcheva  residence  United_States   Output:   Home / News / Car Tech  Aston Martin And Daimler Team Up To Develop Electric Powertrains  Viknesh Vijayenthiran June 24, 2013 Comment Now!  Aston Martin and Mercedes-Benz parent Daimler have signed a Memorandum of Understanding (MoU) for the development of electric powertrains. The two automakers will work together to develop "highly efficient" electric powertrains for future Aston Martin models.  The MoU was signed by Aston Martin CEO Dr. Ulrich Bez and Daimler AG Board Member for Group Research and Mercedes-Benz Cars Development Dr. Thomas Weber during a ceremony at Aston Martin's global headquarters in Gaydon, England.  Under the agreement, Aston Martin will benefit from Daimler's expertise in electric drivetrain technology, which includes the company's pioneering work on hybrid and electric drive systems. In return, Daimler will benefit from Aston Martin's know-how in sports car design and engineering.  The cooperation is part of Aston Martin's Second Century Plan, which outlines the company's strategy for the next 100 years. One of the key elements of the plan is the expansion of its model range with new cars such as the Rapide S four-door sports car, the Vanquish supercar and the upcoming Lagonda

She traveled extensively to raise awareness and funds for children in need, visiting countries such as Ethiopia, Somalia, and Bangladesh. Located at the Apollo Bunder along the historic harbour front, the hotel offers spectacular views of the iconic Gateway of India and the Arabian Sea. Since its doors opened in 1903, the hotel has played host to kings and queens, presidents and prime ministers, captains of industry and stars of stage and screen. It has been the setting for momentous historical events and continues to be the place to see and be seen.  The Taj Mahal Palace comprises two wings – the Palace Wing and the Tower Wing. The Palace Wing was built between 1903 and 1928 by Jamshetji Nusserwanji Tata, the founder of the Tata Group. The Tower Wing was added in 1973. The hotel has 561 rooms and suites, each individually designed and equipped with every modern convenience. Its restaurants offer a variety of cuisines including Indian, Chinese, Japanese, Italian, Middle Eastern, Continental and Mediterranean. Many kids and teenagers keep in touch with each other through social networking websites. Since there are few telephone boxes on the streets, phones seem less important than other things to most British kids. It is the flagship of the University of North Carolina system and considered to be one of the original eight Public Ivy schools. After being chartered in 1789, the university first began enrolling students in 1795, which also allows it to be one of three schools to claim to be the oldest public university in the United States. Why do we need Digital Transformation?  CIOApplications | June 24, 2019  Digital transformation is the integration of digital technologies into all areas of a business, fundamentally changing how a company operates and delivers value to customers. It is also a cultural change that requires organizations to continually challenge their business model, culture, and processes to improve customer experience and compete more effectively. Digital transformation refers to the integration of digital technologies into all areas of a business, resulting in fundamental changes to how a firm operates and delivers value to its customers. It is also a cultural change that requires organizations to continually challenge their business model, culture, and processes to improve the customer experience and compete more effectively. The concept of digital transformation is far-reaching and complex, encompassing everything from cloud computing and big data to mobile devices and social media. As technology evolves at an ever-increasing pace, businesses must adapt to stay relevant and competitive. By embracing digital transformation, companies can increase efficiency, reduce costs, enhance customer experiences, and open up new revenue streams. In short, digital transformation is essential for survival and growth in today's digital age.  More featured news  The future of work: what does it look like for IT leaders? Tom Wolf announced Wednesday that the Pennsylvania Infrastructure Investment Authority (PENNVEST) is now accepting applications for its Small Municipalities/Small Projects Grant Program, which provides funding for drinking water, wastewater, and non-point source projects in small municipalities across the commonwealth.  "All Pennsylvanians deserve access to clean, safe water," said Gov. Wolf. "This program helps smaller municipalities improve their water infrastructure and protect public health. The Small Municipalities/Small Projects Grant Program provides grants of up to $500,000 for drinking water, wastewater, and non-point source projects in municipalities with populations of less than 10,000 people. PENNVEST anticipates awarding approximately $10 million in grants through this round of funding. Input:  The_Two_Towers  author  J._R._R._Tolkien   Output:   Q: How do I get the value of the last element in a list? I have a list with integers and I want to get the value of the last element in the list.  How do I do that?  A: Use the -1 index:  my_list = [1, 2, 3, 4]  last_element = my_list[-1]  print(last_element)  Output:  4  A: You can access the last element of a list by using negative indexing.  Example:  my_list = [1, 2, 3, 4]  last_element = my_list[-1]  print(last_element)  Output:  4  Explanation:  In Python, list indexing starts from 0. When you use a negative index, it counts from the end of the list. So, -1 will refer to the last element of the list.
