Volkswagen Group CEO Martin Winterkorn has announced that the automaker will invest around €5 billion ($6.7 billion) in its electric car program by 2018.  The funds will be used for the development of new electric cars as well as the expansion of charging infrastructure.  Winterkorn made the announcement during a visit to Volkswagen's e-mobility center in Salzgitter, Germany, where the group is currently developing its modular electric drive matrix (MEB) platform.  The MEB platform will underpin a range of electric cars sold under the Volkswagen, Audi, Seat and Skoda brands, with the first model scheduled to enter production in 2016.  The initial investment of €5 billion ($6.7 billion) is part of a total investment of €50 billion ($67 billion) planned by Volkswagen through 2018.  Speaking at the Salzgitter facility, Winterkorn said, "Electromobility is one of the most important future issues for Volkswagen. That is why we are consistently pursuing our electric mobility strategy."  He added

This will be the title displayed at the top of the page and in the URL.  2. **Parent Page**: If your page is part of a hierarchy within your website, select a parent page from the drop-down menu. This will place your new page under the selected parent page in the site navigation.  3. **Template**: Choose a template for your page from the available options. Templates determine the layout and design of your page.  4. **Page Type**: Select the type of page you want to create. Depending on the platform, this could include options such as 'Standard Page', 'Blog Post', 'Contact Us', etc.  5. **Status**: Set the status of your page to either 'Published', 'Draft', or 'Scheduled'. A published page will be visible to all visitors, a draft page will only be visible to you, and a scheduled page will be published at a specific date and time.  6. **SEO Settings**: Configure search engine optimization settings for your page, such as the meta description, meta keywords, and focus keyword. These

Carlyle first invested in China Forestry in May 2007 through its Carlyle Asia Buyout III fund. In September 2007, China Forestry was successfully listed on the Hong Kong Stock Exchange. A: *  *Download the font file (.ttf)  *Copy the font file to app/src/main/assets/fonts folder  *Add following code to build.gradle (Module: app)      android {          ...          sourceSets {              main {                  assets.srcDirs = ['src/main/assets', 'src/main/assets/fonts']              }          }      }  *In your TextView, add the following attribute:  android:fontFamily="@font/your_font_name"  where your_font_name is the name of the font file without the extension.  *If you are using Kotlin, you can do it like this:  textView.typeface = Typeface.createFromAsset(context.assets, "fonts/your_font_name.ttf")  A: Here is how to do it in Kotlin:  *  *Download the font file (.ttf)  *Copy the font file to app/

The study, published in the journal Developmental Psychology, found that adolescents who spent more time using social media reported higher levels of loneliness and lower self-esteem.  Researchers at the University of Haifa in Israel examined the relationship between social media use and emotional development among adolescents aged 13 to 17 years old. The researchers analyzed data collected from two waves of a longitudinal study conducted by the Israeli Center for Developmental Psychology.  In the first wave, students completed questionnaires assessing their social media use, loneliness, and self-esteem. In the second wave, one year later, they were asked to complete the same questionnaires.  The results showed that adolescents who used social media more intensively also reported higher levels of loneliness and lower self-esteem over time.  "These findings suggest that social media use is associated with poorer emotional development during adolescence," said Dr. Gal Gabay, lead author of the study. "While we cannot infer causality from this study, our findings indicate that excessive social media use might have negative consequences for emotional well-being."  The researchers note that

It was written by C. Y. Morgan based on his novel of the same name. The original music score was composed by Frank De Vol. The film is about two high-spirited teenage girls at a Catholic boarding school and their conflicts with the headmistress.  Plot  Mary Clancy and Rachel Devery are students at St. Francis Academy, a strict Catholic boarding school for girls run by the Sisters of Charity. Both Mary and Rachel have a tendency to get into trouble, especially when they team up together. Their escapades attract the disapproval of Mother Superior, the headmistress of the school.  One day, Mary and Rachel decide to go swimming in the river near the school. They are caught by Sister Celeste, who takes away their swimsuits. When Mary and Rachel sneak into the laundry room to retrieve them, they accidentally set off the fire alarm. Mother Superior expels them from the school.  However, Mary and Rachel's mischief catches the attention of Father Conroy, a visiting priest. He realizes that the girls only want to have fun and are not truly bad. He convinces Mother Superior to give them another chance.

The results show that the TiO2 nanoparticles presented high photocatalytic activity with MB degradation up to 95% after 3 h of irradiation. I have two tables named table1 and table2. Both have the same column names but different data. I want to join these two tables and get the result in a new table.  A: You can use UNION ALL to combine the results of both tables into a single result set:  SELECT * FROM table1  UNION ALL  SELECT * FROM table2;  This will return all rows from both tables without removing any duplicates. If you want to remove duplicates, you can use UNION instead of UNION ALL.  However, if you want to perform a JOIN operation (which combines rows from two or more tables based on matching values in one or more columns), you can use the JOIN syntax:  SELECT t1.column1, t1.column2, t2.column1, t2.column2  FROM table1 t1  INNER JOIN table2 t2  ON t1.common_column = t2.common_column;  Replace column1, column2, common_column with the actual column names in your tables. I am trying to make my discord bot send a message every 5 minutes but I have no idea how to do it. Here is my code:  const Discord = require('discord.js');  const client = new Discord.Client();  client.once('ready', () => {      console.log('Ready!');  });  client.on('message', message => {      if (message.author.bot) return;      if (message.content === 'ping') {          message.channel.send('Pong!');      }  });  setInterval(function() {      client.channels.get("CHANNEL ID").send("MESSAGE");  }, 300000);  client.login('TOKEN');  A: In order for your bot to keep running, you will need to use a library called node-schedule. Install it using npm i node-schedule.  After installing it, you can use it like this:  const schedule = require('node-schedule');  let job = schedule.scheduleJob('0 */5 * * *', () => {      client.channels.get("CHANNEL ID").send("MESSAGE");  });  This will run the function inside the arrow function every 5 minutes.

I am trying to call a function when a button is clicked but it doesn't seem to work.  This is my HTML code:  <!DOCTYPE html>  <html>      <head>          <meta charset="UTF-8">          <title>Test</title>          <script src="https://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/3.5.1/jquery.min.js"></script>          <script src="script.js"></script>      </head>      <body>          <button id="myButton">Click me</button>      </body>  </html>  And this is my script.js file:  $(document).ready(function(){      $("#myButton").click(function(){          alert("test");      });  });  When I click the button nothing happens.  A: Your problem is that you didn't close your body tag properly.  You have this:  <body>      <button id="myButton">Click me</button>  </html>  But it should be:  <body>      <button id="myButton">Click me</button>  </body>  A: The problem here is that you forgot to close the body tag.  <

Americans could slash their diet-related greenhouse gas emissions by up to 49 percent if they reduced their meat consumption and ate more plant-based foods, according to a new study published in the journal Nature Food.  Researchers at the University of Michigan analyzed data on food production and consumption in the United States to estimate the climate impact of various dietary changes. They found that replacing beef with chicken, pork, or plant-based foods was the most effective way to reduce greenhouse gas emissions. Replacing beef with chicken resulted in the largest emissions reduction, equivalent to taking 58 million cars off the road for a year.  The researchers also looked at the effect of adopting specific dietary patterns recommended by health organizations, such as the Dietary Guidelines for Americans, the Mediterranean diet, and the Healthy Eating Plate. All of these diets were associated with significant reductions in greenhouse

Apple says Siri can understand more than 20,000 words and phrases, and its creators say they designed it to learn from experience.  “We’ve been working on this for over four years,” said Dag Kittlaus, one of Siri’s co-founders. “It’s something we’ve been passionate about.”  Mr. Kittlaus and Adam Cheyer, also a co-founder, met at SRI International, a nonprofit research institute in Menlo Park, Calif., where they worked on CALO, a Defense Advanced Research Projects Agency project intended to create a personalized artificial intelligence assistant.  In 2007, Mr. Kittlaus and Mr. Cheyer left SRI to start their own company, which they called Siri, after the Norse goddess of wisdom and prophecy. In April 2010, Apple bought Siri for a reported $200 million.  Apple was not the only technology company interested in Siri. Google, Microsoft and Facebook were all vying for the company, according to several people briefed on the negotiations.

A: my_dict = {'a': '1', 'b': '2', 'c': '3', 'd': '4', 'e': '5', 'f': '6', 'g': '7', 'h': '8', 'i': '9', 'j': '0'}  def get_keys(my_dict, value):      return [key for key, val in my_dict.items() if val == value]  print(get_keys(my_dict, '1'))  print(get_keys(my_dict, '3'))  Output:  ['a']  ['c']  A:

The slow adoption rate of Android 8.0 Oreo can be attributed to several factors. Firstly, the fragmented nature of the Android ecosystem means that updates must be developed and approved by both the device manufacturer and the carrier before being rolled out to users. This process can take several months or even over a year in some cases.  Secondly, not all devices are eligible for the update. Lastly, some users may choose not to update their devices due to compatibility issues with certain apps or concerns about battery life and performance.  In summary, the low adoption rate of Android 8.0 Oreo is primarily due to the fragmented nature of the Android ecosystem, limited availability of updates for certain devices, and user preferences.

Input:  Super_Capers  editing  Stacy_Katzman ,  Super_Capers  starring  Michael_Rooker ,  Super_Capers  starring  Tom_Sizemore ,  Super_Capers  language  English_language ,  Super_Capers  runtime  98.0 ,  Super_Capers  budget  2000000.0 ,  Super_Capers  writer  Ray_Griggs_(director)   Output:   Q: How to check if a string contains special characters using regular expressions in Python? I want to check if a string contains special characters (such as $, %, @, etc.) using regular expressions in Python.  How can I do this?  A: You can use re.search with a negative lookahead:  import re  def has_special_char(string):      return bool(re.search(r'(?=.*[^a-zA-Z0-9])', string))  print(has_special_char('abc')) # False  print(has_special_char('$abc')) # True  print(has_special_char('123')) # False  print(has_special_char('%123')) # True  Explanation:  *  *(?=...) is a zero-width positive lookahead assertion  *.* matches any character (except newline) any number of times  *[^a-zA-Z0-9] matches any character that is not a letter or digit  The regex searches for a position in the string where there is a non-alphanumeric character ahead. If such a position is found, the function returns True; otherwise, it returns False.  A: One way is to use a regular expression to match any character that is not alphanumeric

I want to make a listview where every row has a different layout. For example, the first row will have a textview and a button, the second row will have two textviews and so on.  Is there a way to do this without using adapters?  A: No, you can't do this without using an adapter.  Adapters are used to display different views for each item in the list. So if you want to have different layouts for each row, you need to create a custom adapter and override the getView() method to return the desired view for each position. Input:  Liselotte_Grschebina  birthPlace  Karlsruhe ,  Liselotte_Grschebina  nationality  Israel   Output:   The following article contains an answer for the question: What is the full name of the person whose father was a bellfounder? , can you please find it?   In 1835, there were 2,143 gallon tanks built into the walls of the barracks at Portsmouth and Plymouth. In 1853 an additional 63 tanks were installed. In 1863, a decision was made to expand this to include "all barrack rooms", including the Warrant Officers' and Officers' Quarters, and a further 104 tanks were installed. After the Ferro-Concrete Tank Company stopped making these, they were purchased through Brewers of Minworth. These tanks initially held up to 500 imperial gallons (2,300 L; 660 US gal) each; however, later modifications increased this capacity to about 700 imperial gallons (3,200 L; 850 US gal).The installation of the extra tanks resulted in some crowding of the barrack rooms and destruction of many of the original fireplaces. Subsequent modifications in the late 19th and early 20th century resulted in some rooms having the double rows of tanks partly removed. By 1907 there were 162 tanks in use, holding some 63,

The Ellis Island Medals of Honor were created in 1986 by the National Ethnic Coalition of Organizations (NECO) to honor outstanding Americans who have distinguished themselves within their own ethnic groups while exemplifying the values of the American way of life. Each year, NECO selects individuals whose accomplishments in their respective fields and inspired service to our nation are particularly noteworthy.  Mr. Feinberg was recognized for his tireless efforts to save lives through bone marrow and blood stem cell transplantation. Diagnosed with leukemia in 1991, Mr. Feinberg received a life-saving bone marrow transplant from his sister, Sheri. As a result of this experience, he founded The Gift of Life Bone Marrow Foundation in 1991 to help others battling life-threatening illnesses find matching donors. Since its inception, Gift of Life has facilitated more than 6,000 transplants worldwide, making it the largest Jewish and one of the largest independent bone marrow registries in the world.  "It is

Porsche has revealed its latest pair of lightweight sports cars, the 2016 Cayman GT4 and Boxster Spyder, at the 2015 Geneva Motor Show. Both cars are powered by naturally aspirated flat-six engines and feature manual transmissions only.  The last time Porsche offered a naturally aspirated flat-six engine in one of its sports cars was with the 997-generation 911 Carrera S, which was discontinued in 2012. Since then, Porsche's sports cars have been fitted with turbocharged flat-six engines.  But for these two new models, Porsche has reverted back to a naturally aspirated engine due to the purity of the driving experience it provides. The engine is a 3.8-liter unit developed from the one found in the 991-generation 911 Carrera S but tuned to deliver 385 horsepower and 309 pound-feet of torque. Input:  Turn_Me_On_(album)  genre  Punk_blues ,  Turn_Me_On_(album)  producer  The_Honeymoon_Killers_(American_band)   Output:   Home > News > Compliance > DOL Takes Enforcement Action Against Fidelity for ERISA Violations  Compliance November 20, 2019  DOL Takes Enforcement Action Against Fidelity for ERISA Violations  Fidelity Investments has agreed to pay more than $22 million to resolve allegations it violated the Employee Retirement Income Security Act (ERISA).  The U.S. Department of Labor (DOL) has taken enforcement action against Fidelity Investments for violations of the Employee Retirement Income Security Act (ERISA).  According to the DOL, Fidelity failed to disclose conflicts of interest associated with its brokerage window services, which allowed participants in employer-sponsored retirement plans to purchase securities outside of the plan's investment lineup. Specifically, Fidelity did not disclose material conflicts of interest arising from its provision of brokerage window services to employee benefit plans, including that it received revenue sharing payments from certain mutual fund companies when plan participants purchased their funds through the brokerage window.  The DOL says Fidelity also failed to fulfill its fiduciary duties under ERISA by selecting substandard share classes of mutual funds for inclusion in the investment lineups of participant-directed individual account plans without adequately considering lower-cost share classes
